theorem P3_of_dense {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hDense : Dense (A : Set X)) :
    Topology.P3 A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hxA
  -- Since `A` is dense, its closure is `univ`.
  have hClos : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense
  -- Hence the interior of this closure is also `univ`.
  have hInt : interior (closure (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa [hClos] using interior_univ
  -- Any point lies in `univ`, so the desired inclusion holds.
  have : x ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simp
  simpa [hInt] using this

theorem dense_iff_closure_eq_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (A : Set X) ↔ closure (A : Set X) = Set.univ := by
  classical
  constructor
  · intro hDense
    ext x
    constructor
    · intro _hx
      trivial
    · intro _hx
      exact hDense x
  · intro hEq
    intro x
    have : (x : X) ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      trivial
    simpa [hEq] using this
